your spirit of resilience

00:25:01.480 --> 00:25:04.360
and struggle.

00:25:04.360 --> 00:25:08.740
So in 2003, Martha opened
her first restaurant.

00:25:08.740 --> 00:25:12.609
Immediately, it was a success,
very well known, very popular.

00:25:12.609 --> 00:25:13.900
MARTHA ORTIZ: I worked so much.

00:25:13.900 --> 00:25:14.810
You cannot imagine.

00:25:14.810 --> 00:25:18.220
I was the valet parking,
the security, the cook.

00:25:18.220 --> 00:25:19.480
I went to a bank.

00:25:19.480 --> 00:25:24.220
I remember my husband told me,
you will never get the money.

00:25:24.220 --> 00:25:25.990
So I went to a bank.

00:25:25.990 --> 00:25:27.910
I remember that I
bought something

00:25:27.910 --> 00:25:30.580
that I couldn't bought, and
I returned it the other day

00:25:30.580 --> 00:25:33.370
after the bank appointment.

00:25:33.370 --> 00:25:35.980
I remember that I
went very elegant.

00:25:35.980 --> 00:25:38.140
And I asked the man,
I need $1 million.

00:25:38.140 --> 00:25:40.352
And he told me, for what?

00:25:40.352 --> 00:25:44.097
And I said, for a restaurant.

00:25:44.097 --> 00:25:45.055
And they gave it to me.

00:25:45.055 --> 00:25:45.680
SPEAKER: Wow!

00:25:45.680 --> 00:25:47.230
Fantastic.

00:25:47.230 --> 00:25:50.470
MARTHA ORTIZ: I said, here's my
business plan, and I show it,

00:25:50.470 --> 00:25:51.040
you know?

00:25:51.040 --> 00:25:52.950
And they give me
a million dollars.

00:25:52.950 --> 00:25:53.890
This is a true story.

00:25:53.890 --> 00:25:55.390
SPEAKER: That is a
fantastic story--

00:25:55.390 --> 00:25:55.690
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes.

00:25:55.690 --> 00:25:56.481
SPEAKER: --I think.

00:25:56.481 --> 00:25:59.282
MARTHA ORTIZ: And I returned
it with a lot of people

00:25:59.282 --> 00:26:00.490
because I couldn't afford it.

00:26:00.490 --> 00:26:02.605
I need the $1 million
to build the restaurant,

00:26:02.605 --> 00:26:03.730
and it was a great success.

00:26:03.730 --> 00:26:07.790
SPEAKER: It was a fantastic
success, like, it took off.

00:26:07.790 --> 00:26:10.610
However, five years
later, the government--

00:26:10.610 --> 00:26:12.795
MARTHA ORTIZ: I
changed the location.

00:26:12.795 --> 00:26:13.670
SPEAKER: --asked you.

00:26:13.670 --> 00:26:16.330
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes, remember
that I have these beautiful--

00:26:16.330 --> 00:26:18.250
but I need to make it--

00:26:18.250 --> 00:26:21.830
a lot of people was
in saying to me,

00:26:21.830 --> 00:26:25.450
Martha we need to build
this restaurant in Spain,

00:26:25.450 --> 00:26:28.610
and New York, and everything.

00:26:28.610 --> 00:26:32.350
And the space was very
beautiful, but I said,

00:26:32.350 --> 00:26:34.270
I need a private room.

00:26:34.270 --> 00:26:38.249
I need an office in the house.

00:26:38.249 --> 00:26:39.040
I need to build it.

00:26:39.040 --> 00:26:47.380
So I saw the most beautiful,
beautiful corner in Mexico

00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:50.390
where Louis Vuitton
was, and I say,

00:26:50.390 --> 00:26:52.120
OK, Louis Vuitton, let's go.

00:26:52.120 --> 00:26:53.350
You will be Louis Vuitton.

00:26:53.350 --> 00:26:56.331
I will be Aguila y Sol, a
Mexican brand and a woman

00:26:56.331 --> 00:26:56.830
brand.

00:26:56.830 --> 00:26:59.046
So I changed location.

00:26:59.046 --> 00:27:00.755
SPEAKER: You changed
location, and then--

00:27:00.755 --> 00:27:02.962
MARTHA ORTIZ: A beautiful
place, Legoretta made that.

00:27:02.962 --> 00:27:04.130
SPEAKER: Legorreta.

00:27:04.130 --> 00:27:06.520
MARTHA ORTIZ: Made
this space that was--

00:27:06.520 --> 00:27:07.532
SPEAKER: Fantastic art.

00:27:07.532 --> 00:27:08.990
MARTHA ORTIZ:
Beautiful, fantastic.

00:27:08.990 --> 00:27:12.640
And we have a serpent
on the ceilings

00:27:12.640 --> 00:27:15.010
because I don't build
restaurants with architects.

00:27:15.010 --> 00:27:18.550
I always ask artists,
you know, people

00:27:18.550 --> 00:27:25.000
who like opera, or woman
designers, for everything.

00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:28.150
I love that people
from different--

00:27:28.150 --> 00:27:30.910
not just the common
people, no, people

00:27:30.910 --> 00:27:32.099
that is a little bit crazy.

00:27:32.099 --> 00:27:32.890
SPEAKER: And they--

00:27:32.890 --> 00:27:33.936
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes,
a little talent.

00:27:33.936 --> 00:27:35.230
SPEAKER: The spiky ones.

00:27:35.230 --> 00:27:36.120
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes,
the spiky ones.

00:27:36.120 --> 00:27:36.700
I adore that.

00:27:36.700 --> 00:27:40.300
SPEAKER: So the
government asked Martha

00:27:40.300 --> 00:27:41.467
to shut down the restaurant.

00:27:41.467 --> 00:27:43.299
MARTHA ORTIZ: They
closed me, my restaurant.

00:27:43.299 --> 00:27:45.070
SPEAKER: So they asked
her with the excuse

00:27:45.070 --> 00:27:47.311
that you were short
one parking space.

00:27:47.311 --> 00:27:49.060
MARTHA ORTIZ: Less
than one parking space.

00:27:49.060 --> 00:27:50.710
SPEAKER: Less than
one parking space.

00:27:50.710 --> 00:27:52.376
MARTHA ORTIZ: I
remember that afternoon,

00:27:52.376 --> 00:27:55.570
and every time I remember, I
cry because it was so horrible.

00:27:55.570 --> 00:27:57.910
Because people was having lunch.

00:27:57.910 --> 00:28:00.520
They came in, and
they say, we're

00:28:00.520 --> 00:28:02.200
going to close this restaurant.

00:28:02.200 --> 00:28:04.270
And I say, why?

00:28:04.270 --> 00:28:08.880
Because you need to less
than one parking space.

00:28:08.880 --> 00:28:12.730
So I remember that afternoon--

00:28:12.730 --> 00:28:15.530
SPEAKER: I'm sure that it
must have been devastating.

00:28:15.530 --> 00:28:17.420
MARTHA ORTIZ: Devastating.

00:28:17.420 --> 00:28:20.130
They took the people away.

00:28:20.130 --> 00:28:23.930
They took my people away.

00:28:23.930 --> 00:28:26.020
And at the end, I didn't
want to go, they--

00:28:26.020 --> 00:28:29.030
they said to me, we would
leave you here, and I said,

00:28:29.030 --> 00:28:29.730
it's perfect.

00:28:29.730 --> 00:28:31.160
I will die in here.

00:28:31.160 --> 00:28:32.530
I have food.

00:28:32.530 --> 00:28:33.380
I have water.

00:28:33.380 --> 00:28:34.465
I can be here six months.

00:28:34.465 --> 00:28:35.180
SPEAKER: And I know how to.

00:28:35.180 --> 00:28:37.013
MARTHA ORTIZ: And I
will make my resistance.

00:28:37.013 --> 00:28:38.540
I will call the newspapers.

00:28:38.540 --> 00:28:42.770
And they took me
outside by the force.

00:28:42.770 --> 00:28:45.110
SPEAKER: And what do you
think the motivation was?

00:28:45.110 --> 00:28:47.417
MARTHA ORTIZ: I
think I was punished.

00:28:47.417 --> 00:28:49.250
SPEAKER: Because of how
successful you were?

00:28:49.250 --> 00:28:52.460
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of my success,
of course, and I was a woman,

00:28:52.460 --> 00:28:54.180
and I was very young.

00:28:54.180 --> 00:29:00.060
And I cannot tell you it was
this person or this person.

00:29:00.060 --> 00:29:02.870
It was a system because
at the same time,

00:29:02.870 --> 00:29:04.760
a lot of women struggled.

00:29:04.760 --> 00:29:07.050
Carmen Arestegui lost her job.

00:29:07.050 --> 00:29:11.090
A lot of women [INAUDIBLE]
it was, for me, devastating.

00:29:11.090 --> 00:29:12.260
SPEAKER: It was a--

00:29:12.260 --> 00:29:14.250
there was a period
of a clampdown

00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:15.750
on certain local personalities.

00:29:15.750 --> 00:29:18.260
MARTHA ORTIZ: I lost everything
in three days, my work,

00:29:18.260 --> 00:29:23.200
my house, everything.

00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:26.449
SPEAKER: But fast forward
one year, and in one year--

00:29:26.449 --> 00:29:28.240
MARTHA ORTIZ: I remember
that I was crying,

00:29:28.240 --> 00:29:31.350
and a friend of mine--
this is another true story

00:29:31.350 --> 00:29:33.660
how women can help other women.

00:29:33.660 --> 00:29:37.180
She's a very influential
and intelligent lady,

00:29:37.180 --> 00:29:38.040
Denise Dresser.

00:29:38.040 --> 00:29:39.840
SPEAKER: Yeah, of
course, a journalist--

00:29:39.840 --> 00:29:42.270
MARTHA ORTIZ: A journalist in
Mexico and in "The New York

00:29:42.270 --> 00:29:45.930
Times" and a very good friend.

00:29:45.930 --> 00:29:49.260
I remember that I was crying,
crying, crying, crying, crying,

00:29:49.260 --> 00:29:51.210
and she came to my house.

00:29:51.210 --> 00:29:54.700
She's very small, not very
thin, what are you crying about?

00:29:54.700 --> 00:29:57.180
And I said, I lost
everything, everything.

00:29:57.180 --> 00:29:58.710
I lose my restaurant.

00:29:58.710 --> 00:30:00.300
I lose my money.

00:30:00.300 --> 00:30:03.840
I lose everything that
I have worked for.

00:30:03.840 --> 00:30:05.990
And she looked me in the
eyes, and she told me,

00:30:05.990 --> 00:30:09.100
you haven't lost anything.

00:30:09.100 --> 00:30:10.210
You have it here.

00:30:10.210 --> 00:30:11.120
So let's go.

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:13.190
She offered me the door,
and she took me away.

00:30:13.190 --> 00:30:15.410
So I remember I was
crying in the street.

00:30:15.410 --> 00:30:19.010
I have to find a horrible work
to survive, that's the truth.

00:30:19.010 --> 00:30:23.960
I review menus, now casting,
the things that I don't like,

00:30:23.960 --> 00:30:26.930
but I have to do it.

00:30:26.930 --> 00:30:31.250
And I learned how
can you be punished.

00:30:31.250 --> 00:30:33.200
SPEAKER: And that's
what I would like

00:30:33.200 --> 00:30:37.160
for you to share in
retrospective because one

00:30:37.160 --> 00:30:40.460
year after Martha opened her
current restaurant, which

00:30:40.460 --> 00:30:45.680
is the one that catapulted
you to international acclaim,

00:30:45.680 --> 00:30:51.330
but I think that a lot of us
will or have faced setbacks.

00:30:51.330 --> 00:30:52.370
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of course.

00:30:52.370 --> 00:30:56.380
SPEAKER: Now in
retrospective, what do you

00:30:56.380 --> 00:30:59.710
think made you
find your strength

00:30:59.710 --> 00:31:05.290
and just bounce back
with all that force?

00:31:05.290 --> 00:31:09.970
MARTHA ORTIZ: I saw that I
have a social responsibility

00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:12.630
and to be an example
for other women.

00:31:12.630 --> 00:31:14.970
I don't do it just for myself.

00:31:14.970 --> 00:31:19.950
I remember to see my cooks,
chef, what are we going to do?

00:31:19.950 --> 00:31:20.880
We don't have work.

00:31:20.880 --> 00:31:23.370
And I say, we will find a work.

00:31:23.370 --> 00:31:24.450
Don't worry.

00:31:24.450 --> 00:31:28.950
And I remember that that's
why the name is Dulce Patria.

00:31:28.950 --> 00:31:31.410
People doesn't know,
that's my private joke

00:31:31.410 --> 00:31:36.300
because I think that my homeland
is sweeter than my government.

00:31:36.300 --> 00:31:38.360
SPEAKER: Yes, dulce patria
means sweet homeland.

00:31:38.360 --> 00:31:39.652
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes, it's my--

00:31:39.652 --> 00:31:41.130
it's my private joke.

00:31:41.130 --> 00:31:46.020
And-- and the logo, it's
a woman with a flame

00:31:46.020 --> 00:31:48.190
like an Amazon and a horse.

00:31:48.190 --> 00:31:50.880
So if they do it again,
I will do it again.

00:31:50.880 --> 00:31:53.970
I told them, if you're going to
close me the restaurant again,

00:31:53.970 --> 00:31:59.500
I will open again, and we will
die maybe first you or me,

00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:01.770
but we will keep like this, no?

00:32:01.770 --> 00:32:02.370
You close.

00:32:02.370 --> 00:32:03.300
I will open.

00:32:03.300 --> 00:32:05.010
You close me, I will open.

00:32:05.010 --> 00:32:06.240
And [INAUDIBLE].

00:32:06.240 --> 00:32:10.230
So I felt in that
moment, that I have

00:32:10.230 --> 00:32:13.740
to get a story not just
for me because I have to be

00:32:13.740 --> 00:32:16.480
an example for a lot of women.

00:32:16.480 --> 00:32:19.495
I was in the supermarket,
and they come crying with me.

00:32:19.495 --> 00:32:21.720
I cannot believe this, chef.

00:32:21.720 --> 00:32:23.520
We are very sorry.

00:32:23.520 --> 00:32:24.850
What are you going to do?

00:32:24.850 --> 00:32:27.150
And I said, we have
to do it together.

00:32:27.150 --> 00:32:29.010
We're going to build it again.

00:32:29.010 --> 00:32:30.900
So I make Dulce Patria.

00:32:30.900 --> 00:32:32.010
I don't know which--

00:32:32.010 --> 00:32:33.260
now I see it back.

00:32:33.260 --> 00:32:35.514
If it happened to me, I
don't know, but I say,

00:32:35.514 --> 00:32:36.180
I have to do it.

00:32:36.180 --> 00:32:36.990
I have to do it.

00:32:36.990 --> 00:32:38.100
I have to do it.

00:32:38.100 --> 00:32:39.810
I divorced the twice.

