And they were-- he
can choose from,

00:36:13.340 --> 00:36:15.390
because he was thin, remember?

00:36:15.390 --> 00:36:16.360
SPEAKER: He was.

00:36:16.360 --> 00:36:18.443
MARTHA ORTIZ: People said,
maybe it was like this.

00:36:18.443 --> 00:36:20.360
No, he needed to choose.

00:36:20.360 --> 00:36:21.230
They were warriors.

00:36:21.230 --> 00:36:22.820
They need to make a strong.

00:36:22.820 --> 00:36:26.070
And then the Spanish came
with all the Arabic influence.

00:36:26.070 --> 00:36:29.000
So I think it melted perfectly.

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:35.990
And then in all the convents
in the Baroque time,

00:36:35.990 --> 00:36:39.680
they rebuild, and they
make this Mexican identity,

00:36:39.680 --> 00:36:42.230
like the mole, like
the pipian like--

00:36:42.230 --> 00:36:44.860
SPEAKER: It's like twice it
has been like [INAUDIBLE]..

00:36:44.860 --> 00:36:46.359
MARTHA ORTIZ: Like
all these sauces.

00:36:46.359 --> 00:36:52.250
And I have an idea
of, at the beginning--

00:36:52.250 --> 00:36:56.750
and I always said that when
Hernan Cortes came to Mexico

00:36:56.750 --> 00:37:00.020
or La Nueva Espana in that
moment that they called it,

00:37:00.020 --> 00:37:01.980
and he saw La Malinche--

00:37:01.980 --> 00:37:04.670
Malinche was this beautiful
and wonderful lady

00:37:04.670 --> 00:37:07.016
that everybody
looks as a traitor

00:37:07.016 --> 00:37:08.390
because she was
very intelligent.

00:37:08.390 --> 00:37:10.400
But she wasn't a traitor.

00:37:10.400 --> 00:37:14.330
She was the mother
of Mexico in a way.

00:37:14.330 --> 00:37:18.750
When he tries her, he adored her
because it tastes like the sun,

00:37:18.750 --> 00:37:19.290
salty.

00:37:19.290 --> 00:37:20.420
Have you tried?

00:37:20.420 --> 00:37:22.640
Have you put your hand in
the sun and then tried?

00:37:22.640 --> 00:37:24.200
It's a little bit salty.

00:37:24.200 --> 00:37:26.690
So I think he get in love
because she was salty

00:37:26.690 --> 00:37:29.670
because she tasted like the sun.

00:37:29.670 --> 00:37:38.240
And I have that idea that
this melting, wonderful parts

00:37:38.240 --> 00:37:40.220
all over the world that
they were in Mexico.

00:37:40.220 --> 00:37:42.920
That's why Mexican
gastronomy is so rich.

00:37:42.920 --> 00:37:45.050
That's why our
culture is so rich.

00:37:45.050 --> 00:37:47.600
That's why we have the artists
that we have, the movie

00:37:47.600 --> 00:37:49.850
directors right now.

00:37:49.850 --> 00:37:51.530
They are amazing, why?

00:37:51.530 --> 00:37:55.620
Because we have this imagination
and this idea of beauty.

00:37:55.620 --> 00:38:00.740
Before I come to London, I saw
"Roma," the new film of Cuaron.

00:38:00.740 --> 00:38:01.460
SPEAKER: Cuaron.

00:38:01.460 --> 00:38:02.210
MARTHA ORTIZ: Wow!

00:38:02.210 --> 00:38:07.130
An amazing story-- what a
profound story about these--

00:38:07.130 --> 00:38:08.020
this Mexico--

00:38:08.020 --> 00:38:09.830
SPEAKER: And so proud--

00:38:09.830 --> 00:38:11.600
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of
what they are doing.

00:38:11.600 --> 00:38:12.700
SPEAKER: The work
they are doing.

00:38:12.700 --> 00:38:13.470
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes.

00:38:13.470 --> 00:38:16.820
But they have this imagination,
and that imagination

00:38:16.820 --> 00:38:19.510
is through food too.

00:38:19.510 --> 00:38:21.640
SPEAKER: I wouldn't like
to hijack your time.

00:38:21.640 --> 00:38:22.860
So I want to have the--

00:38:22.860 --> 00:38:25.510
I'll give the
opportunity, anybody to--

00:38:25.510 --> 00:38:26.510
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of course.

00:38:26.510 --> 00:38:27.830
SPEAKER: --ask any question or--

00:38:27.830 --> 00:38:30.080
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of course, and
thank you for being here.

00:38:30.080 --> 00:38:35.220
SPEAKER: --share anything that
you would like to ask Martha?

00:38:35.220 --> 00:38:37.420
If not, I'll carry on.

00:38:37.420 --> 00:38:39.459
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of course.

00:38:39.459 --> 00:38:40.000
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:40.360
MARTHA ORTIZ: Hi.

00:38:40.360 --> 00:38:42.443
AUDIENCE: I went to your
country a few months ago,

00:38:42.443 --> 00:38:44.590
and I had the Maria
from Mexico dessert.

00:38:44.590 --> 00:38:45.340
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes.

00:38:45.492 --> 00:38:47.200
AUDIENCE: It was
actually one of the best

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:48.370
desserts I've ever had.

00:38:48.370 --> 00:38:49.369
MARTHA ORTIZ: Thank you.

00:38:49.369 --> 00:38:51.970
AUDIENCE: But you were
saying how it changes,

00:38:51.970 --> 00:38:53.770
and sometimes it's
not on the menu.

00:38:53.770 --> 00:38:56.050
Is it always the same,
the actual dessert,

00:38:56.050 --> 00:38:58.360
or does the dessert
itself change?

00:38:58.360 --> 00:39:02.270
MARTHA ORTIZ: In Mexico,
we change it every month.

00:39:02.270 --> 00:39:05.560
And here, we change
it every time

00:39:05.560 --> 00:39:08.110
that we have on a special menu.

00:39:08.110 --> 00:39:12.330
Now Maria is this new one.

00:39:12.330 --> 00:39:14.510
Maria went to Mictlan.

00:39:14.510 --> 00:39:21.820
Mictlan is the land of the
dead for the Aztecs here.

00:39:21.820 --> 00:39:23.950
But in Mexico, she
goes all the way.

00:39:23.950 --> 00:39:25.150
She went there.

00:39:25.150 --> 00:39:26.780
She returned with victory.

00:39:26.780 --> 00:39:28.150
She is alive.

00:39:28.150 --> 00:39:32.800
And, now, she makes a
government of all the stars.

00:39:32.800 --> 00:39:35.650
So she creates an
eclipse in Mexico.

00:39:35.650 --> 00:39:38.140
So everybody says,
she's powerful.

00:39:38.140 --> 00:39:39.880
And I say, of course, yes.

00:39:39.880 --> 00:39:42.345
She can government
even the stars.

00:39:42.345 --> 00:39:43.470
SPEAKER: That's incredible.

00:39:43.470 --> 00:39:46.030
So when-- when do
have the [INAUDIBLE]??

00:39:46.030 --> 00:39:47.030
MARTHA ORTIZ: This one--

00:39:47.030 --> 00:39:47.990
Maria, Maria by Mictlan--

00:39:47.990 --> 00:39:48.670
SPEAKER: It's currently.

00:39:48.670 --> 00:39:49.878
MARTHA ORTIZ: It's currently.

00:39:49.878 --> 00:39:51.380
In Mexico, she [INAUDIBLE].

00:39:51.380 --> 00:39:51.880
SPEAKER: OK.

00:39:51.880 --> 00:39:54.033
MARTHA ORTIZ: I have
more hands [INAUDIBLE]..

00:39:54.033 --> 00:39:57.910
AUDIENCE: OK, so if I go back,
I can't have the same dessert.

00:39:57.910 --> 00:39:59.410
MARTHA ORTIZ: You
want the same one?

00:39:59.410 --> 00:40:00.040
AUDIENCE: The same dessert.

00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:01.590
MARTHA ORTIZ: You want
Mary Comes to London?

00:40:01.590 --> 00:40:02.205
AUDIENCE: It was the--

00:40:02.205 --> 00:40:03.820
MARTHA ORTIZ: Just ask
us in the reservation.

00:40:03.820 --> 00:40:05.020
You have the right people.

00:40:05.020 --> 00:40:06.560
Stephen will make it happen.

00:40:06.560 --> 00:40:07.950
He will tell the kitchen.

00:40:07.950 --> 00:40:10.270
Or Gabriella will
say to Elliott,

00:40:10.270 --> 00:40:13.430
no problem, no problem.

00:40:13.430 --> 00:40:15.010
Thank you very much.

00:40:15.010 --> 00:40:17.915
And I'm very pleased
that you liked Maria.

00:40:17.915 --> 00:40:18.790
Maria is a character.

00:40:18.790 --> 00:40:19.765
It's not a dessert.

00:40:19.765 --> 00:40:23.020
It's like she's a writer.

00:40:23.020 --> 00:40:24.656
She's everything.

00:40:24.656 --> 00:40:28.025
AUDIENCE: Why did you decide
to open a restaurant in London?

00:40:28.025 --> 00:40:28.900
MARTHA ORTIZ: London?

00:40:28.900 --> 00:40:31.000
AUDIENCE: Yeah, and
maybe you said it, sorry.

00:40:31.000 --> 00:40:32.350
MARTHA ORTIZ: I think it's--

00:40:32.350 --> 00:40:33.970
no, I didn't say it.

00:40:33.970 --> 00:40:36.890
I adore London since
I was a little girl.

00:40:36.890 --> 00:40:41.150
I remember that I came here
with my parents, and I really

00:40:41.150 --> 00:40:43.480
I adored it because
it was the first time

00:40:43.480 --> 00:40:47.220
that I tried Indian food and
these kind of new flavors.

00:40:47.220 --> 00:40:50.940
So as I said, all
the seeds stay here.

00:40:50.940 --> 00:40:55.030
Then the group that
I'm working with,

00:40:55.030 --> 00:40:57.910
they went to Mexico,
see different chefs,

00:40:57.910 --> 00:41:02.380
and they decided that I could
be successful in London maybe

00:41:02.380 --> 00:41:05.260
because I have, I think,
this imagination ingredient

00:41:05.260 --> 00:41:06.820
that I adore.

00:41:06.820 --> 00:41:10.170
So it was built
in the both ways.

00:41:10.170 --> 00:41:14.244
SPEAKER: And I think I will
exhort everybody to go--

00:41:14.244 --> 00:41:15.910
MARTHA ORTIZ: Because
it can taste nice.

00:41:15.910 --> 00:41:18.920
SPEAKER: Because
it is quite unique.

00:41:18.920 --> 00:41:22.545
I think it is beyond what
you would usually think of--

00:41:22.545 --> 00:41:23.545
MARTHA ORTIZ: Of course.

00:41:23.545 --> 00:41:25.330
SPEAKER: --in Mexican cuisine.

00:41:25.330 --> 00:41:26.650
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes, of course.

00:41:26.650 --> 00:41:29.770
SPEAKER: It is
remarkably different

00:41:29.770 --> 00:41:31.201
and incredibly authentic.

00:41:31.201 --> 00:41:32.200
MARTHA ORTIZ: Thank you.

00:41:32.200 --> 00:41:32.700
Thank you.

00:41:32.700 --> 00:41:36.370
SPEAKER: So I definitely
encourage you to try.

00:41:36.370 --> 00:41:38.410
AUDIENCE: You mentioned
that you're working now

00:41:38.410 --> 00:41:41.740
on a new book with
a different concept

00:41:41.740 --> 00:41:43.780
really empowering a
certain number of women

00:41:43.780 --> 00:41:45.010
and their story.

00:41:45.010 --> 00:41:46.640
What about your previous books?

00:41:46.640 --> 00:41:48.220
Were they also--

00:41:48.220 --> 00:41:50.620
MARTHA ORTIZ: No, they
are are not cookbooks.

00:41:50.620 --> 00:41:52.810
I'm making these
because I think I

00:41:52.810 --> 00:41:56.770
have to share my experience of
Aguila y Sol that was terrible

00:41:56.770 --> 00:41:59.470
in a way, but in
a positive part.

00:42:02.140 --> 00:42:08.810
And I think because I make
so much of this effort,

00:42:08.810 --> 00:42:10.310
and I was telling
you that I believe

00:42:10.310 --> 00:42:12.810
that life can be
like your recipe,

00:42:12.810 --> 00:42:16.620
building these ingredients,
that I have to share it.

00:42:16.620 --> 00:42:20.570
And I would love not to be just
the only one that shared it.

00:42:20.570 --> 00:42:26.330
So I'm asking people that I
highly respect in Mexico that

00:42:26.330 --> 00:42:30.890
have been through difficult
times, maybe worse than mine,

00:42:30.890 --> 00:42:31.850
but they make--

00:42:31.850 --> 00:42:33.890
they're my kind of
heroines, you know?

00:42:33.890 --> 00:42:35.750
I believe in the power of woman.

00:42:35.750 --> 00:42:39.110
I said, I like Wonder Woman,
you know, this kind of Wonder

00:42:39.110 --> 00:42:40.640
Womans that we have in Mexico.

00:42:40.640 --> 00:42:44.720
Sometimes I say, this
woman has lost a child.

00:42:44.720 --> 00:42:50.630
They are here to
ask for justice,

00:42:50.630 --> 00:42:53.210
and that's the
work of every day.

00:42:53.210 --> 00:42:57.050
That's very-- that's hard.

00:42:57.050 --> 00:42:59.312
That's hard.

00:42:59.312 --> 00:43:00.770
AUDIENCE: How long
does it actually

00:43:00.770 --> 00:43:03.350
take to train all the
chefs in the restaurant

00:43:03.350 --> 00:43:06.260
before they actually bring
on the plate what you expect?

00:43:06.260 --> 00:43:08.380
And are you actually
cooking yourself sometimes?

00:43:08.380 --> 00:43:09.600
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes, of
course, [INAUDIBLE]..

00:43:09.600 --> 00:43:10.700
AUDIENCE: But here
in London, like--

00:43:10.700 --> 00:43:11.990
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yeah,
sometimes, yes, of course.

00:43:11.990 --> 00:43:12.590
AUDIENCE: So when
are you there again?

00:43:12.590 --> 00:43:13.360
When can we go?

00:43:13.360 --> 00:43:14.255
MARTHA ORTIZ: I'm--

00:43:14.255 --> 00:43:15.650
OK.

00:43:15.650 --> 00:43:17.660
I'm coming back in February.

00:43:17.660 --> 00:43:21.500
I'm opening a new restaurant
in Mexico, very interesting,

00:43:21.500 --> 00:43:24.220
because it's a cafe.

00:43:24.220 --> 00:43:27.380
And I think we are
losing all the bread

00:43:27.380 --> 00:43:30.800
Mexican tradition
that I adore, even

00:43:30.800 --> 00:43:34.790
the names we call it,
cocoles, purequitas, conchas,

00:43:34.790 --> 00:43:37.010
and novias.

00:43:37.010 --> 00:43:38.510
You know, all these
beautiful names.

00:43:38.510 --> 00:43:41.930
So I'm opening a cafe with
all the traditional bread--

00:43:41.930 --> 00:43:42.890
SPEAKER: Oh, wow!

00:43:42.890 --> 00:43:45.950
MARTHA ORTIZ: --with
pulque, with chochitos,

00:43:45.950 --> 00:43:48.650
with all these kind of beauties.

00:43:48.650 --> 00:43:52.280
I'm going to open it in January.

00:43:52.280 --> 00:43:56.090
I think after Aguila y Sol, I
was a little bit frightened,

00:43:56.090 --> 00:43:58.610
you know, to--

00:43:58.610 --> 00:43:59.870
I think it was unconscious.

00:43:59.870 --> 00:44:03.510
So I stay in my small
castle, you know,

00:44:03.510 --> 00:44:10.790
you put like a barrier,
but I decide last year

00:44:10.790 --> 00:44:14.210
that I want to achieve
better things than I have.

00:44:14.210 --> 00:44:18.260
And I start--

00:44:18.260 --> 00:44:20.790
I'm going to open three
restaurants next year.

00:44:20.790 --> 00:44:22.740
And, one, it's
going to be amazing,

00:44:22.740 --> 00:44:23.870
because it's a theater.

00:44:23.870 --> 00:44:25.640
It's not a restaurant.

00:44:25.640 --> 00:44:27.500
We will have a place.

00:44:27.500 --> 00:44:30.820
And the place will go
through [INAUDIBLE]..

00:44:30.820 --> 00:44:35.900
And the menu is
going to be built

00:44:35.900 --> 00:44:39.960
with one like Laura Esquivel,
"Like Water to Chocolate."

00:44:39.960 --> 00:44:42.230
So we're going to
build this menu.

00:44:42.230 --> 00:44:45.320
We're going to-- it's going
to be like a testing menu,

00:44:45.320 --> 00:44:49.460
but even the things that
you're going to eat with

00:44:49.460 --> 00:44:52.160
is not going to be conventional.

00:44:52.160 --> 00:44:54.034
It's going to be
very interesting.

00:44:54.034 --> 00:44:55.700
AUDIENCE: You're a
foreigner, and you're

00:44:55.700 --> 00:44:59.210
a woman in a city that
is a very tough city.

00:44:59.210 --> 00:45:03.650
What has been your biggest
challenge because I--

00:45:03.650 --> 00:45:07.340
even, like, here the
chefs that we hear from,

00:45:07.340 --> 00:45:09.020
there's hardly a lot of--

00:45:09.020 --> 00:45:12.980
hardly any women
in your world, so

00:45:12.980 --> 00:45:14.412
has that been challenging here?

00:45:14.412 --> 00:45:15.620
MARTHA ORTIZ: Yes, of course.

00:45:15.620 --> 00:45:21.260
I think the most difficult
thing here for me is that I'm--

00:45:21.260 --> 00:45:22.440
not all the time.

00:45:22.440 --> 00:45:26.420
That's the first thing that if
I want to achieve something,

00:45:26.420 --> 00:45:28.880
I maybe would need
to have more time,

00:45:28.880 --> 00:45:34.430
you know, educating
people about Mexico

00:45:34.430 --> 00:45:36.665
because I think one
of the challenges

00:45:36.665 --> 00:45:41.690
is that people get confused
with Tex-Mex food and Mexican

00:45:41.690 --> 00:45:44.000
and more right now, you know?

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:49.620
And what I believe for
me that it's a challenge,

00:45:49.620 --> 00:45:51.140
sometimes, it's even--

00:45:54.290 --> 00:45:55.040
hello, Martha.

00:45:55.040 --> 00:45:56.930
No, it's hello, chef.

00:45:56.930 --> 00:45:59.030
It's different, no?

00:45:59.030 --> 00:46:03.380
So I think it's a way of--

00:46:03.380 --> 00:46:07.910
of I was saying in
Mexico, they call

00:46:07.910 --> 00:46:09.630
me chef because they
see me every day,

00:46:09.630 --> 00:46:11.630
and they know that I have
control of everything,

00:46:11.630 --> 00:46:14.900
of the fire, of the
fireman, of everything,

00:46:14.900 --> 00:46:17.480
but here, I do the menu.

00:46:17.480 --> 00:46:19.530
I work with great people.

00:46:19.530 --> 00:46:21.740
But I don't have
the time, you know?

00:46:21.740 --> 00:46:24.020
And that's difficult
for me sometimes.

00:46:24.020 --> 00:46:26.300
So I have to create--

00:46:26.300 --> 00:46:29.330
what I want to do
the next time is

00:46:29.330 --> 00:46:32.930
make the chefs come
to Mexico and maybe

00:46:32.930 --> 00:46:36.140
have more environment
of what we are doing.

00:46:36.140 --> 00:46:39.170
I'm making this
dish of this blue

00:46:39.170 --> 00:46:45.402
because I adore this painting
of Remedios Varo in this museum.

00:46:45.402 --> 00:46:47.360
So we're going to take
this woman in Wonderland

00:46:47.360 --> 00:46:49.820
in this plate and do it right.

00:46:49.820 --> 00:46:52.790
That's what I'm going to
do, coming and going, not

00:46:52.790 --> 00:46:53.930
just coming.

00:46:53.930 --> 00:46:57.050
I think they have
to have, you know,

00:46:57.050 --> 00:46:58.670
the blood, the spirit of Mexico.

00:47:01.430 --> 00:47:06.680
SPEAKER: Do you
think that that is--

00:47:06.680 --> 00:47:11.960
particularly like
the educating part,

00:47:11.960 --> 00:47:14.442
how do you approach it
beyond your restaurant.

00:47:14.442 --> 00:47:15.900
Obviously, the
restaurant is there.

00:47:15.900 --> 00:47:17.300
And there's the food.

00:47:17.300 --> 00:47:18.320
How-- how is--

00:47:18.320 --> 00:47:20.570
MARTHA ORTIZ: In Mexico, I
do it completely different.

00:47:20.570 --> 00:47:24.460
Sometimes, Mexico,
the chefs, they maybe

00:47:24.460 --> 00:47:26.790
didn't have a formal education.

00:47:26.790 --> 00:47:32.999
So on Sundays, we give them
Mexican history lessons.

00:47:32.999 --> 00:47:33.790
SPEAKER: Oh, great.

00:47:33.790 --> 00:47:38.800
MARTHA ORTIZ: So they feel
proud about what we are.

00:47:38.800 --> 00:47:42.770
I invite very interesting
people, sometimes artists,

00:47:42.770 --> 00:47:47.330
so they will know that we have
these figurative tradition

00:47:47.330 --> 00:47:49.410
in Mexico.

00:47:49.410 --> 00:47:51.500
And now we're going to have--

00:47:51.500 --> 00:47:53.670
I think that is
going to be amazing,

00:47:53.670 --> 00:47:54.980
because I love flowers.

00:47:54.980 --> 00:47:58.100
But I don't like flowers
just because they are nice.

00:47:58.100 --> 00:48:01.340
I adore them because they
have, I think, a spirit.

00:48:01.340 --> 00:48:05.300
And in Mexico in the shamans
and in traditional medicine,

00:48:05.300 --> 00:48:07.230
they use it to cure you.

00:48:07.230 --> 00:48:12.860
So we're going to invite
an expert in flowers

00:48:12.860 --> 00:48:17.930
