00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:08.690
say, I don't like this, because
it has this taste, this, this.

00:50:08.690 --> 00:50:11.780
But about the style, I
never asked to other cooks.

00:50:11.780 --> 00:50:13.140
I go with the artist.

00:50:13.140 --> 00:50:15.770
I remember that I built
this beautiful relation

00:50:15.770 --> 00:50:17.900
with Ricardo Legorreta.

00:50:17.900 --> 00:50:21.040
And I remember that I go
running to his house, I show,

00:50:21.040 --> 00:50:21.990
do you like it?

00:50:21.990 --> 00:50:24.230
And he told me-- he was the
best architect in Mexico

00:50:24.230 --> 00:50:25.580
and say, no.

00:50:25.580 --> 00:50:28.280
So I'd get back to
the kitchen and build

00:50:28.280 --> 00:50:29.480
the salad in another way.

00:50:29.480 --> 00:50:30.530
Do you like it?

00:50:30.530 --> 00:50:31.580
No.

00:50:31.580 --> 00:50:36.920
So I rem-- because I love
to hear from other artists.

00:50:36.920 --> 00:50:39.380
Sometimes I invite
Guillermo Kahlo, that

00:50:39.380 --> 00:50:42.680
is this great Mexican
photographer, and I say,

00:50:42.680 --> 00:50:45.320
do you think these
has this power

00:50:45.320 --> 00:50:47.420
and this beauty of Mexico?

00:50:47.420 --> 00:50:50.400
Yes, Martha, but
think in this way.

00:50:50.400 --> 00:50:54.830
So I always love to hear
that from another artist

00:50:54.830 --> 00:50:59.810
more than another cook because
I think it's, as you said,

00:50:59.810 --> 00:51:02.750
it's a temptation to be
like another person and more

00:51:02.750 --> 00:51:04.880
in this global world.

00:51:04.880 --> 00:51:09.080
And I think you need
to listen, and I go--

00:51:09.080 --> 00:51:12.570
and I never go to another
restaurant to have inspiration.

00:51:12.570 --> 00:51:14.300
I love to go to museums.

00:51:14.300 --> 00:51:16.580
I can be-- today I saw
that it was [INAUDIBLE]

00:51:16.580 --> 00:51:18.446
in the National--

00:51:18.446 --> 00:51:20.800
in the Royal Academy.

00:51:20.800 --> 00:51:25.140
And I love the gold and the
purple of [INAUDIBLE] together.

00:51:25.140 --> 00:51:27.110
I want to see that because I--

00:51:27.110 --> 00:51:30.170
and then I can go to Alexander
McQueen and say this is black,

00:51:30.170 --> 00:51:31.400
and she's a woman--

00:51:31.400 --> 00:51:34.880
she's a woman designer and say,
oh, Simone Rocha is putting,

00:51:34.880 --> 00:51:36.850
you know, flowers,
all over the--

00:51:36.850 --> 00:51:38.420
in her Instagram.

00:51:38.420 --> 00:51:43.820
I love that kind of inspiration,
and when I make the black menu

00:51:43.820 --> 00:51:45.470
that I'm taking
to San Francisco,

00:51:45.470 --> 00:51:50.680
I read Cesar Vallejo,
this poet that I adore,

00:51:50.680 --> 00:51:55.550
that said so much love.
but nothing against death.

00:51:55.550 --> 00:51:57.170
And I start on that point.

00:51:57.170 --> 00:52:00.590
So I get inspired by
that kind of things.

00:52:00.590 --> 00:52:02.090
I can go to a
museum, and I start

00:52:02.090 --> 00:52:04.803
crying because I think it's
too beautiful, you know?

00:52:04.803 --> 00:52:06.960
People look at me like this.

00:52:06.960 --> 00:52:11.430
But I cry because I think
it's overwhelming, you know?

00:52:11.430 --> 00:52:13.050
I think where is
the beauty, I think

00:52:13.050 --> 00:52:18.570
that when a person can create
beauty or more than that,

00:52:18.570 --> 00:52:22.380
I think that our
lives have value

00:52:22.380 --> 00:52:25.230
when you can share beauty.

00:52:25.230 --> 00:52:28.620
And beauty can be
defined a lot of things,

00:52:28.620 --> 00:52:35.320
but beauty can be in love,
in power, in paintings.

00:52:35.320 --> 00:52:40.960
But I think that's our mission
in life to share beauty.

00:52:40.960 --> 00:52:42.190
SPEAKER: Wow.

00:52:42.190 --> 00:52:45.160
I'm inspired now, Martha.

00:52:45.160 --> 00:52:49.140
MARTHA ORTIZ: That's what
